Hello,

Engine.copy(...) only makes a copy of the job directory. It doesn&#39;t build
or launch the job, which means it doesn&#39;t build any beans or anything. You
could still edit your new crawler-beans.cxml before launching the job.

It is possible to
 build the job and then fiddle with the beans. Something like

Engine.copy(...)
;

job = Engine.getJob(...)
;

job.validateConfiguration(); // i.e. build
metadataBean = job.getJobContext().getBean(&quot;metadata&quot;)
;


Then you could fiddle with the properties of metadataBean.

But overriding the class at that stage is probably not feasible, because
the bean is already built and wired into other beans that use it. So you
probably want to edit your cxml before building the job.

Noah

